{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1ab91251-1d65-451a-8d66-5708655adbf1","content":"Analyzing crash dumps is outside the scope of the tools I have available (the `dump-collect` skill is only for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them). Here's how you can analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n**Options:**\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Then use commands like `clrstack`, `pe` (print exception), `dumpheap`, etc.\n\n2. **Visual Studio** (Windows): File → Open → File → select the `.dmp` → \"Debug with Managed Only\"\n\n3. **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   # or\n   lldb --core your-file.dmp\n   ```\n\n**Quick triage commands** inside `dotnet-dump analyze`:\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `dso` — dump stack objects\n\nWould you like help setting up any of these tools?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1df27428-4723-4ccc-9dac-33208044513c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description says it's for **collecting** crash dumps, and explicitly states \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing.\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":403},"id":"72239a15-5698-4ed8-a1f2-2d6eca9d9be9","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:01:59.409Z","parentId":"e1e3a881-7c7a-4a83-8da3-cf1b3c444eef"}
